        <p>Contrast this with <m>t=0</m>, where <m>a_\text{T}  = 0</m> and <m>a_\text{N}  = 4/\sqrt{2}\approx 2.82</m>. Here the particle's speed is not changing and all acceleration is in the form of direction change.</p>
      </solution>
