    <example xml:id="ex_tannorm7">
      <title>Analyzing projectile motion</title>
      <statement>
        <p>A ball is thrown from a height of 240ft with an initial speed of 64ft/s and an angle of elevation of <m>30^\circ</m>. Find the position function <m>\vrt</m> of the ball and analyze <m>a_\text{T}</m> and <m>a_\text{N}</m>.<index><main>projectile motion</main></index></p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>Using <xref ref="idea_projectile">Key Idea</xref> of <xref ref="sec_vvf_motion">Section</xref> we form the position function of the ball:
          <me>
            \vrt = \la \big(64\cos(30^\circ) \big)t, -16t^2+\big(64\sin(30^\circ) \big)t+240\ra,
          </me>
          which we plot in <xref ref="fig_tannorm7b">Figure</xref>.</p>

        <figure xml:id="fig_tannorm7b" >
          <caption>Plotting the position of a thrown ball, with 1s increments shown.</caption>
          <!-- START figures/fig_tannorm7b.tex -->
          <image xml:id="img_tannorm7b" >
            <description></description>
            <latex-image-code>
              <![CDATA[
              \begin{tikzpicture}[>=stealth]
              \begin{axis}[%
              %
			%x=.37\marginparwidth,
			%y=.37\marginparwidth,
